## 1.3 Settings Sanitization

Currently, [register_setting()](file:///d:/Z_Work/Sayan/sugar%20story/auto-location-woocommerce/includes/class-alw-admin.php#33-54) is called with **no `sanitize_callback`** in [class-alw-admin.php](file:///d:/Z_Work/Sayan/sugar%20story/auto-location-woocommerce/includes/class-alw-admin.php):

```php
register_setting( 'alw_settings_group', 'alw_store_lat' );  // No sanitization!
```

This means an admin (or a CSRF exploit targeting an admin) could save:
- Latitude = `999` (impossible — valid range is -90 to 90)
- Rate per KM = `-5` (negative rate — would give customers money back!)
- Round method = `exec` (if we ever used `call_user_func` on this, it would be catastrophic)

### Implementation

A `sanitize_callback` for each setting:

```php
register_setting( 'alw_settings_group', 'alw_store_lat', [
    'type'              => 'number',
    'sanitize_callback' => [ $this, 'sanitize_latitude' ],
]);
```

```php
public function sanitize_latitude( $value ) {
    $value = floatval( $value );
    if ( $value < -90 || $value > 90 ) {
        add_settings_error( 'alw_store_lat', 'invalid_lat',
            __( 'Latitude must be between -90 and 90.', 'auto-location-woocommerce' )
        );
        return get_option( 'alw_store_lat' ); // Return old value, reject new one
    }
    return $value;
}
```

### Validation Rules per Setting

| Setting | Validation Rule |
|---------|----------------|
| `alw_google_api_key` | `sanitize_text_field()`, non-empty, alphanumeric + dashes |
| `alw_store_lat` | Float, clamped to `[-90, 90]` |
| `alw_store_lng` | Float, clamped to `[-180, 180]` |
| `alw_free_km` | Float, `>= 0` |
| `alw_max_km` | Float, `> 0`, must be `>= alw_free_km` |
| `alw_rate_per_km` | Float, `>= 0` |
| `alw_round_method` | Strict whitelist: `ceil`, `floor`, `round` |

